                             TYMCOM-X BASE (EBUS)                             ________ ____ ______

            If the BASE (EBUS) gets hung or crashes, the PDP-10  will  complain
       with  an  INFO stopcode NOBASE, and state that the BASE (EBUS) should be
       reloaded.

           "%%EVENT stopcode NOBASE at dd-mmm-yyy hh:mm:ss"
           "No response from base.  Please reload it.  PDP-10 is still up."

       The above will output until the base is reloaded or the Operator presses
       the "INI" button on the BASE.  If after approximately SIXTY (60) seconds
       there is no print out on the Console TTY, press the button again.


                                         NOTE

           Recyle the PDP-10 and reload  the  BASE  (EBUS)  if  the  second
           attempt fails.



            If this procedure (pressing the "INI" button) works, the  following
       message will print out to the Console TTY twice:

           "%%EVENT stopcode BASEOK at dd-mmm-yyy hh:mm:ss"
           "Code in base is version 2.02 - debug flag is OFF"

            After receiving the above message, see if circuits have been  built
       by  running  TELECO.  TELECO any file under the username of OPER to OPER
       on another system.  If you can, then everything is okay.   If  not,  you
       will need to recycle the PDP-10 and reload the BASE (EBUS).

            Make sure your Shift Supervisor is fully informed of the  situation
       as well as NOVADYNE.










