                             DEPOSITING INTO MA 30                             __________ ____ __ __

            There are three basic  reasons  for  the  abrupt  crashing  of  the
       TYMCOM-X with a deposit into memory address 30:

            1) The SYSTEM is HUNG.

            2) Leaving the system up would result  in  DISK  STRUCTURE  DAMAGE.
            This  may  be  indicated by rapidly accumulating HDEV (Hard DEVice)
            errors,  by  '?TRANSMISSION  ERROR'S  from  more  than  one  system
            commands  or  by messages on the CTY regarding bad SATS, RIBS, MFD,
            "critical files" etc.

            3) Some catastophe like fire, flood, earthquake etc.

            The following symptoms DO NOT indicate the need for a deposit  into
       MA 30:

            1) You cannot login to the host due to

                    FRAME CAPACITY EXCEEDED
                    HOST OUT OF PORTS
                    ACCESS BARRED
                    (ANY OTHER REASON PROVIDING A MESSAGE)

       These messages mean exactly what they  say  and  are  not  fatal  errors
       requiring the deposit into 30.

            2) The system response is slow.

            3) You cannot kill a 'stuck' job with TAKEIT.

            For these situations, there  may  be  a  condition  which  warrants
       immediate  attention,  but they do not warrant the immediate destruction
       that occurs with the 1 in 30.  Even if it  is  necessary  to  bring  the
       system  down,  make  every  effort  to use the TAKEIT program to do this
       'gracefully'.

            In some cases, problems with the  network  (especially  during  net
       takeover)  can give the false impression of a host hangup.  You can test
       this by trying the long form of login:

                  'PLEASE LOGIN:'OPER:NN (CR)
                  'PASSWORD:' (PSWD);(CR)

       If you dont get the prompt for 'PASSWORD:', the problem is  probably  in
       the  net,  not  in  the host.  Remember that inability to login does not
       affect those users who are already logged into the system.  Call Network
       Control  to  find  out  if there is any network condition which could be
       preventing logins.





